  "body": "[comment]: # (Please replace ... with your information. Remove < and >)\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\n[comment]: # (Feature or Bug? i.e Type: Bug)\r\n*Type*: Bug\r\n\r\n[comment]: # (Describe the feature you would like, or briefly summarise the bug and what you did, what you expected to happen, and what actually happens. Sections below)\r\n*Summary*: Timestamps in 1-1 chat are shown accordingly to the timezone instead of actual time for received message if timezone and time are different on Android device \r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nTimestamp on the recipient's side is shown accordingly to the selected time, not timezone\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\nTimestamp on the recipient's side is shown accordingly to his timezone \r\n\r\n<img width=\"607\" alt=\"1\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/29711298/45036154-6014e380-b064-11e8-9951-99751a074674.png\">\r\n\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n[comment]: # (Describe how we can replicate the bug step by step.)\r\n\r\n- On the device A go to Settings -> Date & Time\r\n- Disable Automatic time zone (if it's selected)\r\n- Set time zone and time manually to be different (for example time zone GMT+2 and time GMT+4)\r\n- Open Status and create an account on device A\r\n- On the device B enable Automatic time zone (Settings -> Date & Time)\r\n- Open Status and create an account on device B\r\n- Add device A and device B accounts as contacts of each other \r\n- Send a message from the device B (with automatic time zone) to the device A in 1-1 chat\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n* Status version: release build 0.9.27 (7623), node v0.13.1 \r\n* Operating System: Real device OnePlus 5, Android 8.1.0\r\n\r\n",
